# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Table 1: functools.partial class name attributes
#
# Wave 264 theme: functools.partial is a C-extension type (Modules/_functoolsmodule.c).
# Its __name__ and __qualname__ are both 'partial' (length 7: p-a-r-t-i-a-l).
# type(functools.partial).__name__ is 'type' because partial is a class.
# type(functools.partial.__doc__).__name__ is 'str' — the docstring is a Python
# string. functools.partial.__new__.__qualname__ is 'partial.__new__' (len 15)
# and type(functools.partial.__new__).__name__ is 'builtin_function_or_method'
# because __new__ on a C-extension type is a C-level static method.
#
# functools.partial.__name__ == 'partial'
# len(functools.partial.__name__) == 7
# functools.partial.__qualname__ == 'partial'
# type(functools.partial.__doc__).__name__ == 'str'
# functools.partial.__new__.__qualname__ == 'partial.__new__'
# len(functools.partial.__new__.__qualname__) == 15
# type(functools.partial.__new__).__name__ == 'builtin_function_or_method'
#
# New to extra118.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

